{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"protocol"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"CursorProtocol"},{"kind":"text","text":" : "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"ObjectProtocol","preciseIdentifier":"s:10GLibObject0B8ProtocolP"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"overview","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Cursors are immutable objects, so once you created them, there is no way"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to modify them later. You should create a new cursor when you want to change"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"something about it."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Cursors by themselves are not very interesting: they must be bound to a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"window for users to see them. This is done with [method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gdk.Surface.set_cursor"},{"type":"text","text":"]"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"or [method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gdk.Surface.set_device_cursor"},{"type":"text","text":"]. Applications will typically"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"use higher-level GTK functions such as [method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gtk.Widget.set_cursor"},{"type":"text","text":"] instead."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Cursors are not bound to a given [class"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gdk.Display"},{"type":"text","text":"], so they can be shared."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"However, the appearance of cursors may vary when used on different"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"platforms."}]},{"anchor":"Named-and-texture-cursors","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Named and texture cursors"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"There are multiple ways to create cursors. The platformâ€™s own cursors"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"can be created with [ctor"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gdk.Cursor.new_from_name"},{"type":"text","text":"]. That function lists"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the commonly available names that are shared with the CSS specification."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Other names may be available, depending on the platform in use. On some"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"platforms, what images are used for named cursors may be influenced by"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the cursor theme."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Another option to create a cursor is to use [ctor"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gdk.Cursor.new_from_texture"},{"type":"text","text":"]"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and provide an image to use for the cursor."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To ease work with unsupported cursors, a fallback cursor can be provided."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"If a [class"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gdk.Surface"},{"type":"text","text":"] cannot use a cursor because of the reasons mentioned"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"above, it will try the fallback cursor. Fallback cursors can themselves have"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"fallback cursors again, so it is possible to provide a chain of progressively"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"easier to support cursors. If none of the provided cursors can be supported,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the default cursor will be the ultimate fallback."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CursorProtocol"},{"type":"text","text":" protocol exposes the methods and properties of an underlying "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GdkCursor"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The default implementation of these can be found in the protocol extension below."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"For a concrete class that implements these methods and properties, see "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Cursor"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Alternatively, use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CursorRef"},{"type":"text","text":" as a lighweight, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"unowned"},{"type":"text","text":" reference if you already have an instance you just want to use."}]}]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"sections":[],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/gdk\/cursorprotocol"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"relationshipsSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/Gdk\/4GLib14PointerWrapperP","doc:\/\/Gdk\/10GLibObject0B8ProtocolP"],"kind":"relationships","title":"Inherits From","type":"inheritsFrom"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/Gdk\/documentation\/Gdk\/Cursor","doc:\/\/Gdk\/documentation\/Gdk\/CursorRef"],"kind":"relationships","title":"Conforming Types","type":"conformingTypes"}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/Gdk\/documentation\/Gdk\/CursorProtocol","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"abstract":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GdkCursor"},{"type":"text","text":" is used to create and destroy cursors."}],"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"protocol"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"CursorProtocol"}],"title":"CursorProtocol","roleHeading":"Protocol","role":"symbol","symbolKind":"protocol","externalID":"s:3Gdk14CursorProtocolP","modules":[{"name":"Gdk"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"CursorProtocol"}]},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/Gdk\/documentation\/Gdk"]]},"topicSections":[{"title":"Instance Properties","identifiers":["doc:\/\/Gdk\/documentatio